According to CNN, Kaepernick has donated $100,000 to a coronavirus relief fund created to help Black and Latinx communities impacted by the public health crisis.
Colin Kaepernick announced he was contributing $100,000 to a coronavirus relief fund, which will go toward aiding black and brown communities affected by the pandemic.
https://t.co/fC7rplXqeA — CNN (@CNN) April 17, 2020The fund is a part of Kaepernick’s Know Your Rights Camp campaign; a movement designed to advance the liberation of Black and brown communities through education-focused, self-empowerment initiatives.
“That’s why we’ve established the “Know Your Rights” Camp COVID-19 Relief Fund to help address these issues.”Many influential individuals in sports and entertainment are leading initiatives to support the Black community during the pandemic.
“This campaign is for underserved communities experiencing life-changing events related to or triggered by the COVID-19 pandemic,” said Henson.